    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@howy1993 \r\nIn this design, the incentive to relay is on the `gasPrice * gasLimit` and `reward` delta. \r\nA smart relay network (or dapp relayer) would pick transactions with the highest delta, meaning that for lower ERC-20 fees, you should also seek the lowest possible `gasPrice * gasLimit` to increase the delta. The relayers entity can publicly refuse meta-txs with low deltas.\r\n\r\nI think It's easier and cheaper to overload the network without this protocol. And yes, dapps can set limits too.",
